# Post-Initial LOO-CV Plan

**Date:** March 2026  
**Status:** Initial LOO-CV run completing — do not modify pipeline until finished.

---

## Context

The initial LOO-CV run used VR-TSST EEG data (44 participants, `dataset.h5`) as a
proxy pretraining dataset. Several methodological issues were identified **during**
the run. This document records the planned corrective steps before drawing any
conclusions.

Known issues with the initial run — results should be treated as a baseline only:

| Issue | Severity | Detail |
|---|---|---|
| Condition ordering in dataset export | **Critical** | `sorted(task_events.items())` sorts alphabetically by name, not by recording onset — counterbalancing is ignored; all participants appear as HIGH→LOW regardless of actual order |
| Participant exclusions incomplete | **Critical** | P34 (RMS outlier), P37 (likely reversed labels), P21 (elevated RMS), P16 (missing LOW block) identified by sanity check — not excluded from initial run |
| Per-epoch z-score + InstanceNorm2d double normalisation | Minor | Redundant; removes amplitude signal useful for MWL decoding |
| Temporal fine-tune test split | Major | End-of-block epochs are systematically different (fatigue, drift) |
| Overlapping windows in fine-tune split | Major | 87.5% overlap → adjacent windows share 224/256 samples; random split causes data leakage |
| Alphabetical val-participant split during pretraining | Minor | P40–P44 may be systematically different from earlier participants |

