## Step 1 — Run sanity check (immediately after LOO finishes)

**Do not modify any pipeline file before this step.**

Run `scripts/check_mwl_dataset.py` against the current `dataset.h5` and the
completed fold results:

```powershell
C:\vr_tsst_2025\.venv\Scripts\python.exe scripts/check_mwl_dataset.py
```

**What to look for:**

- Class balance per participant (expected ~50/50)
- Label ordering (expected: block-structured — 4 × 3-minute conditions)
- Amplitude outliers (high RMS participants may explain low-AUC folds)
- Logistic regression AUC per participant (θ+α features) — this is the
  signal-existence baseline independent of EEGNet
- Correlation between logistic AUC and EEGNet AUC — if uncorrelated, the
  issue is the pipeline not the data

**Decision gate:** if logistic regression gives mean AUC < 0.55, the
VR-TSST→MATB transfer signal is genuinely weak and the ceiling for any
EEGNet improvement is low. Adjust expectations accordingly before proceeding.

