## Step 3 — Select representative participants for rapid iteration

Select **3 participants** spanning the performance distribution from the
initial run — do not cherry-pick high-AUC participants:

| Type | Criterion | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| High AUC | Top quartile (e.g. P07) | Confirm changes don't break good cases |
| Mid AUC | Median fold | The typical case |
| Low AUC | Bottom quartile (e.g. P20) | Most diagnostic for pipeline issues |

Use this 3-participant subset for all subsequent single-change tests
(Steps 4–5). Each subset LOO run takes ~5–10 minutes vs ~2 hours for
the full 44-fold run.

**Important:** subset AUC numbers are for directional comparison only
(did it go up or down?). Do not report absolute AUC from 3 participants.

---

## Step 4 — Validate corrected pipeline on subset

Run the 3-participant subset LOO with:
- New `dataset.h5` (step_s=0.5, per-channel z-score)
- Gap-buffered stratified random fine-tune split (gap_windows=4)
- Random seeded val-participant split during pretraining

Compare directionally to initial run results for the same 3 participants.
If mean AUC is flat or lower, investigate before proceeding to Step 5.

---

## Step 5 — Set ceiling goal and systematic improvement plan

### Ceiling estimate

Use sanity check logistic regression AUC (Step 1) as the upper bound
for what EEGNet can achieve on this data.

| Logistic AUC (mean) | Interpretation | EEGNet ceiling target |
|---|---|---|
| > 0.65 | Strong signal — EEGNet underperforming | 0.62–0.68 |
| 0.55–0.65 | Moderate signal — some room to improve | 0.58–0.63 |
| < 0.55 | Weak signal — limited by data not model | ~0.55 (accept and move on) |

### Systematic tweak order

Test **one change at a time** on the 3-participant subset.
Do not stack multiple changes before evaluating each individually.

| Priority | Tweak | Rationale | Risk |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Random seeded val-participant split | Removes alphabetical bias in pretraining early stopping | Low |
| 2 | `F1=16` in EEGNet (currently F1=8) | Doubles temporal filter capacity | Low–Medium |
| 3 | Longer pretraining patience (30 → 40) | May be stopping before optimal generalisation | Low |

Stop when mean subset AUC plateaus or reaches the ceiling estimate.
Do not chase marginal gains beyond the ceiling.

---

## Step 6 — Overnight full LOO with best improvements

Once the subset results identify a stable improvement (AUC lift > 0.02
on all 3 subset participants), run the full 44-fold LOO overnight.

**Before running:**
- Save initial run results as `output/matb_pretrain/loo_cv_results_v1/`
- Save corrected run results as `output/matb_pretrain/loo_cv_results_v2/`
- Update `docs/loso_cv_methodology.md` with the changes made

**Success criterion for moving to real MATB data collection:**
- Mean LOO AUC (full mode) > 0.58 across 44 folds, OR
- Decision made that VR-TSST signal ceiling is ~0.55 and the pipeline
  is validated as working correctly at that level

Either outcome is acceptable — the goal of this experiment is pipeline
validation, not maximising AUC on VR-TSST data.

